<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2022-03-21T14:40:20.256+01:00" lasteditedby="Adam" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Joint</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Joints<keyword>Ball-Joint</keyword><keyword>Pin-Joint</keyword><keyword>Slide-Joint</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Kinematic-Pairs</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Popup Box"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:143px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-Pop-Joints.ipp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:297px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Joints</text><text style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">&#32;</text>(<text style="color:#800080;">DE Gelenk</text>) constrain two <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Part" styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Parts</link> to move relative to each other in a defined way. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">There are three <text styleclass="Popup Box2">joints</text> in <text styleclass="VariableName-IT" style="font-size:10pt;">MechDesigner</text><text style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">:</text></para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:8pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">A<text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">&#32;</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Pin-Joint" styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Pin-Joint</link>&#32;<image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>the same as a Revolute-Joint, the R Joint in a Dyad</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">A <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Slide-Joint" styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Slide-Joint</link>&#32;<image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> the same as a Prismatic-Joint, the P Joint in a Dyad</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">A <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Ball-Joints" styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Joint</link><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements"> -</text> the same as a Spherical Joint, the S Joint in a Dyad</li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2" style="width:297px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Each letter in a <text styleclass="Popup Box2">DYAD</text> is a <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Joint</text> - the letters in the <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Dyads</text> are: <text styleclass="Popup Box2">R</text>, <text styleclass="Popup Box2">P </text>and <text styleclass="Popup Box2">S</text> refer to <text styleclass="Popup Box2">R</text>evolute, <text styleclass="Popup Box2">P</text>rismatic and <text styleclass="Popup Box2">S</text>pherical, respectively.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
